Program: Discovery
Title: Matters Of The Heart - part two
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry6h
Last Broadcast Date: 24 September 2002
How Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) has given doctors a new understanding of the heart. Cardiologists at the Royal Brompton Hospital in London explain aspects of their complicated jobs. Presenter: Geoff Watts.